{
  "texts": [
    "Performance of RL controllers to unseen ReThe RL controller is tested at different Reynolds numbers, in order to examine its generalisability to environment changes.",
    "The controllers have been trained at Re = 100 with both FM and PM conditions, and tested at Re = 80, 90, 100, 110, 120, 150.",
    "The controllers were trained further at Re = 150, denoted as continual learning (CL), and tested again at Re = 150.As shown in figure 14, in both PM-Dynamic and FM-Static cases, the RL controllers are able to reduce drag by η = 64.68 % in the worst case, when Re is close to the training point at Re = 100, i.e.",
    "the test cases with Re = 80, 90, 100, 110, 120.",
    "However, when applying the controllers trained at Re = 100 to an environment at Re = 150, the drag reduction drops to η = 41.98 % and η = 74.04 % in the PM-Dynamic and FM-Static cases, respectively."
  ]
}